OSM Exploratory Data Analysis

1 File Download

  • We manually downloaded all the files from https://hdyc.neis-one.org/.
  • Type osm id
  • right mouse click and go to line 89
  • Copy it to a text editor and
  • Save it as a .json file

2 1. File import

2.1 Call files into the R environment

filenames <- list.files("Contributors/", pattern="*.json", full.names=TRUE) 
# Import data
osm_json <-filenames %>% 
  map(read_json) %>% 
  reduce(bind_rows) %>% 
  mutate(document.id = row_number())

2.3 Select variables

Using enter_object(), gather_object(), and spread_values(), you can create and customise data.frames.

# Glance at the first index
osm_json %>% 
  enter_object('contributor') %>% 
  spread_values(name = jstring(name),
                 uid = jstring(uid),
                traces = jstring(traces),
                blocks = jstring(blocks)
                )

osm_json %>% 
  spread_all() %>% 
  as_data_frame.tbl_json() -> osm_tibble

2.4 Import Excel files

survey_original <- readxl::read_xlsx("OSM survey data.xlsx") %>% select(-c(`(Found) Username`, ...6, `6.a. If you selected Other, please specify:`))

survey_original %>% 
  rename(username = `1. What is your OpenStreetMap Username?`,
         gender = `2. What gender do you identify as?`,
         age = `3. What is your age?`,
         country_residence = `4. What is your country of residence?`,
         nationality = `5. What is your nationality?`,
         education = `6. What is your highest level of education?`
         ) -> survey

# Create a dataframe that contains all users names
data.frame(filenames) -> usernames_df

usernames_df %<>% 
  rename(username = filenames) %>% 
  mutate(username = gsub("Contributors//","", .$username)) %>% 
  mutate(username = gsub(".json","", .$username)) %>% 
  left_join(survey, by = "username")
dem_table <- table(usernames_df$gender, usernames_df$age)
dem_table %>% 
  t() %>% 
  as.data.frame.matrix() %>% 
  knitr::kable()

3 Days of Week

3.1 Data cleaning and summary table

### Days
osm_json %>%
  as_tbl_json(drop.nulljson = T) %>% 
  enter_object('changesets') %>%
  spread_values(days = jstring(days)) %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  pull(2)-> days

data.frame(days) %>% 
  mutate(days = gsub("\\|$","", days)) %>%
  separate_rows(days, sep = "[|]") %>%
  separate(days, c("Sun", "Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", "Fri", "Sat"), ",") %>% 
  mutate(across(where(is.character), as.numeric)) -> days_df


days_df %>% summary()

usernames_df %>%  
  bind_cols(days_df) %>% 
  drop_na(gender) %>% 
  mutate(age = fct_relevel(age, "18-24", "25-29", "30-34", "35-39", "40-44", "45-49", "50-54", "60-64", "70 or over")) -> days_df_combined

3.2 Outcome

days_df_combined %>%
  select(gender, Sun:Sat) %>% 
  pivot_longer(!gender, names_to = "days", values_to = "count") %>% 
  group_by(gender) %>% 
  summarise(mean = mean(count))
## # A tibble: 2 x 2
##   gender  mean
##   <chr>  <dbl>
## 1 Female  421.
## 2 Male    679.
## men have contributed 258 days higher than women on average

days_df_combined %>% 
  group_by(gender) %>% 
  summarise_if(is.numeric, mean, na.rm = TRUE)
## # A tibble: 2 x 8
##   gender   Sun   Mon   Tue   Wed   Thu   Fri   Sat
##   <chr>  <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>
## 1 Female  283.  470.  467.  475.  486.  440.  326.
## 2 Male    736.  668.  647.  630.  643.  667.  761.
days_df_combined %>%
  select(gender, age, Sun:Sat) %>% 
  rowwise() %>% 
  mutate(total_days = sum(c_across(where(is.numeric)), na.rm = T)) %>% 
  select(gender, age, total_days) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = gender, y = total_days, fill = gender)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  theme_bw()

days_df_combined %>%
  select(gender, age, Sun:Sat) %>%
  group_by(gender) %>% 
  summarise_if(is.numeric, mean, na.rm = TRUE) %>% 
  reshape2::melt(id = "gender", variable.name = "Days", value.name = "Value") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Days, y = Value, group = gender, colour = gender)) +

  geom_line() +

  select(gender, age, Sun:Sat) %>%

4 OSM Contribution during the hours of day

4.1 Summary Statistics

osm_json %>%
  as_tbl_json(drop.nulljson = T) %>% 
  enter_object('changesets') %>%
  spread_values(hours = jstring(hours)) %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  pull(2)-> hours

data.frame(hours) %>% 
  mutate(hours = gsub("\\|$","", hours)) %>%
  separate_rows(hours, sep = "[|]") %>%
  separate(hours, c("h01", "h02", "h03", "h04", "h05", "h06",
                    "h07", "h08", "h09", "h10", "h11", "h12",
                    "h13", "h14", "h15", "h16", "h17", "h18",
                    "h19", "h20", "h21", "h22", "h23", "h24"
  ), ",") %>%
  mutate(across(where(is.character), as.numeric)) -> hours_df

usernames_df %>% 
  bind_cols(hours_df) %>% 
  drop_na(gender) %>% 
  mutate(age = fct_relevel(age, "18-24", "25-29", "30-34", "35-39", "40-44", "45-49", "50-54", "60-64", "70 or over")) -> hours_df_combined
hours_df_combined %>%
  select(gender, h01:h24) %>% 
  pivot_longer(!gender, names_to = "Hours", values_to = "count") %>% 
  group_by(gender) %>% 
  summarise(mean = mean(count))
## # A tibble: 2 x 2
##   gender  mean
##   <chr>  <dbl>

hours_df_combined %>%

  group_by(gender, Hours) %>% 
  summarise(mean = mean(count)) %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from = gender, values_from = mean) %>%

hours_df_combined %>%

  geom_line() +

  theme_bw()

hours_df_combined %>%
  select(gender, age, h01:h24) %>%
  group_by(age, gender) %>% 
  summarise_if(is.numeric, mean, na.rm = TRUE) %>% 
  reshape2::melt(id = c("gender","age"), variable.name = "Days", value.name = "Value") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Days, y = Value, group = gender, colour = gender)) +
  geom_point() +

5 Bbboxes: How geospatially wide do people contribute in OSM

osm_json %>%
  as_tbl_json(drop.nulljson = T) %>% 
  enter_object('changesets') %>%
  spread_values(number = jstring(bboxs)) %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  pull(2)-> bboxs


data.frame(bboxs) %>% 
  mutate(bboxs = gsub("\\|$","", bboxs)) %>%
  separate_rows(bboxs, sep = ";") %>%
  filter(row_number() %% 3 == 1) %>% 
  mutate(across(where(is.character), as.numeric)) -> bboxs_df

usernames_df %>% 
  bind_cols(bboxs_df) %>% 
  drop_na(gender) %>% 
  mutate(age = fct_relevel(age, "18-24", "25-29", "30-34", "35-39", "40-44", "45-49", "50-54", "60-64", "70 or over")) -> bboxs_df_combined
bboxs_df_combined %>%
  select(gender, age, bboxs) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = gender, y = bboxs, fill = gender)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  theme_bw()

bboxs_df_combined %>%
  select(gender, age, bboxs) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = gender, y = bboxs, fill = age)) +
  geom_boxplot()

6 Tags

osm_json %>% 
  enter_object('nodes') %>% 
  spread_values(created = jstring(c),
                modified = jstring(m),
                deleted = jstring(d),
                lastmod = jstring(lm)) %>% 
  as_data_frame.tbl_json() %>% 
  mutate(across(where(is.character), as.numeric)) -> nodes_df


osm_json %>% 
  enter_object('ways') %>% 
  spread_values(created = jstring(c),
                modified = jstring(m),
                deleted = jstring(d),
                lastmod = jstring(lm)) %>% 
  as_data_frame.tbl_json() %>% 
  mutate(across(where(is.character), as.numeric)) -> ways_df



usernames_df %>% 
  bind_cols(nodes_df) %>% 
  drop_na(gender) %>% 
  mutate(age = fct_relevel(age, "18-24", "25-29", "30-34", "35-39", "40-44", "45-49", "50-54", "60-64", "70 or over")) -> nodes_df_combined

usernames_df %>% 
  bind_cols(ways_df) %>% 
  drop_na(gender) %>% 
  mutate(age = fct_relevel(age, "18-24", "25-29", "30-34", "35-39", "40-44", "45-49", "50-54", "60-64", "70 or over")) -> ways_df_combined
library(viridis)

nodes_df_combined %>%
  select(gender, created:lastmod) %>% 
  group_by(gender) %>% 
  summarise_all(list(nodes = mean)) -> nodes_radar_df

ways_df_combined %>%
  select(gender, created:lastmod) %>% 
  group_by(gender) %>% 
  summarise_all(list(ways = mean)) -> ways_radar_df



nodes_radar_df %>% 
  left_join(ways_radar_df, name = "gender") %>% 
  pivot_longer(!gender, names_to = "Type", values_to = "Count") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(Type, Count, fill = Type)) +
  geom_bar(position="dodge", stat="identity") +
  scale_fill_viridis(discrete = T, option = "E") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels= scales::comma) +
  facet_wrap(~gender) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position="none",
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1))
